
[1]poet

   PO'ET, n. [L. poeta. See Poem.]

   1. The author of a poem; the inventor or maker of a metrical
   composition.

   A poet is a maker, as the word signifies; and he who cannot make, that
   is, invent,hath his name for nothing.

   2. One skilled in making poetry, or who has a particular genius for
   metrical composition; one distinguished for poetic talents. Many write
   verses who cannot be called poets.
